        conseils: "The Bordeaux–Toulouse journey is heavily used for business (Airbus, aerospace industry). For business travellers, our saloons offer comfort for working during the journey (personal Wi-Fi, USB ports). A stop at Moissac (10 min detour from the A62) is highly recommended: the abbey and Romanesque cloister (UNESCO) are among France's finest. In Toulouse, the Place du Capitole and surrounding shopping streets are the heart of urban life. The Cité de l'Espace (full day, €25) is unmissable for families. Cassoulet is Toulouse's signature dish: the best are at Le Colombier, Chez Émile or the Victor Hugo market (restaurant floor). Toulouse violets are the typical souvenir (sweets, perfumes, liqueurs). For a return, we offer the Toulouse → Bordeaux journey at the same rate.",
