        conseils: "The Tomato Festival (mid-August, 3 days) is Marmande's major event: float parade, recipe contests, producers' market and festivities. Book your taxi on the festival weekend. The Renaissance cloister of Notre-Dame church (free access) is an architectural surprise — a hidden gem not to be missed. The Marmande market (Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday mornings, Place du Marché and hall) is excellent for local produce: tomatoes in summer, strawberries, Lot-et-Garonne kiwis. The Château de Duras (25 km, 20 min) is worth a detour: medieval castle with panoramic views over the Dropt valley, and the Côtes de Duras appellation produces excellent dry white wines. Our drivers can combine Marmande with a stop at La Réole (30 km), a small town on the Garonne with France's oldest town hall and a Benedictine priory.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TER Bordeaux–Marmande costs €15-18 and takes about 55 min (direct, 6-8 trains/day). It is a good rail connection. The TaxiNeo taxi at €120 — €155 is relevant for groups (3-4 passengers: €30-52 per person), families and those wanting to combine Marmande with stops (Langon, La Réole, Duras). By car, expect €10 fuel and €8 tolls. The taxi offers door-to-door and flexibility, particularly useful during the Tomato Festival when parking is difficult.",
