        routeDescription: "165 km — approximately 1h45 via the A63 towards Bayonne, Capbreton-Hossegor exit",
        introduction: "Hossegor (officially Soorts-Hossegor) is the undisputed surf capital of Europe. This seaside resort in the Landes, nestled between the Atlantic Ocean and its marine lake, attracts the world's best surfers every year for the Quiksilver Pro France (World Surf League Championship Tour stage, October). The Estagnots beach and La Gravière are world-famous for their powerful tubular waves, created by the unique geomorphology of the sandy seabed. Beyond surfing, Hossegor possesses a singular architectural charm inherited from the 1920s-1930s: sumptuous Basque-Landes villas with tile roofs, built by regionalist architects, line the lake and pine-shaded avenues. The Hossegor lake, connected to the ocean by the Boudigau canal, is a 150-hectare saltwater body offering calm swimming, water sports and walks. The Centrale district, with its surf shops, bars and restaurants, is the vibrant heart of the resort. Hossegor and its twin Capbreton (linked by the Boucarot canal) together form the most dynamic seaside hub on the Landes coast. Surf brands (Quiksilver, Rip Curl, Billabong) have established their European headquarters in the Soorts area, making Hossegor a true hub for the surf and sportswear industry. The surrounding pine forest offers kilometres of cycle paths and hiking trails.",
        itineraire: "From Bordeaux, your driver takes the southern ring road then the A63 towards Bayonne-Spain. The motorway crosses the great Landes de Gascogne forest, one of Western Europe's largest forest areas: maritime pines as far as the eye can see, clearings and fern undergrowth. You pass Salles, Belin-Béliet and the Landes de Gascogne regional natural park. After Labouheyre and Castets, the Capbreton-Hossegor exit appears. Arrival at Hossegor is via a departmental road through the coastal forest. A63 tolls amount to approximately €14. The journey is fast and smooth except on July-August weekends (holiday departures). An alternative via the coast (D652 through Biscarrosse, Mimizan, Moliets) takes 3h but is spectacular, through the finest Landes beaches.",
        conseils: "The Quiksilver Pro France (October) is the year's global surf event at Hossegor: free beach access to watch the world's best surfers. Book your taxi well in advance during this period. For surfing, south beaches (La Gravière, La Centrale) are for experienced surfers; north beaches (Les Culs Nuls, Les Bourdaines) are better for beginners. Surf schools offer lessons for all levels (€35-45 per session). The Hossegor lake is perfect for family swimming (calm, shallow water on the Parc Rosny side). The Hossegor market (Tuesday and Saturday mornings, hall and Place des Landais) is a treat: foie gras, duck, Landes kiwis, pastis landais (cake). In the evening, the Centrale district comes alive with tapas bars, fish restaurants and a festive atmosphere. The Jean des Sables restaurant (Michelin-starred) is the top local dining address.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TER Bordeaux–Dax then Dax–Hossegor shuttle costs €20-25 but requires a connection and about 2h30 total. The XL'R bus (line 10) connects Dax to Hossegor in 40 min for €2, but with only 4 departures/day. The TaxiNeo taxi at €210 — €270 is ideal for groups of surfers (3-4 passengers: €53-90 per person) with boards and luggage. We carry up to 3 surfboards in our vehicles (notify when booking). By car, expect €18 fuel and €14 tolls. The taxi offers direct door-to-door service, essential when travelling with surf equipment.",
