        conseils: "Biscarrosse offers three worlds: specify your exact destination when booking (Ville, Lac or Plage). Cazaux-Sanguinet lake is ideal for families: supervised swimming, calm freshwater, sandy beaches. The ocean beach (Biscarrosse-Plage) is magnificent but respect supervised swimming zones (rip currents). The Seaplane Museum (€7, 1h30 visit) is fascinating, even for non-aviation enthusiasts. The International Seaplane Rally (every 2 years, May) is a unique event: landings, demonstrations and exhibitions. The Biscarrosse market (Tuesday and Friday mornings) offers Landes products: foie gras, confit, pastis landais, forest honey. Cycle paths are excellent: rent a bike and ride from lake to ocean (10 km through the forest). In the evening, Biscarrosse-Plage offers a few ocean-facing bars and restaurants.",
