        conseils: "The Sanctuaries are open daily, free entry. The Grotto of Massabielle is accessible 24/7. The torchlight processions (9pm, every evening April to October) are a highlight, even for non-believers: thousands of candles in the night. The baths (bathing in the spring water) are free but expect 1-2h wait in peak season. The castle and Pyrenean Museum (€7, 2h visit) offer an interesting cultural counterpoint. The Pic du Jer funicular (€12, 6 min ride) offers the finest panorama in the region. For nature lovers, Lake Lourdes (3 km away) is a pleasant walk. In winter, ski resorts are close: Cauterets (30 min), Luz-Ardiden (30 min), Grand Tourmalet (45 min). The Lourdes market (Saturday morning, les Halles) offers local products: spit-roasted cake, nougat, mountain cheese.",
