        conseils: "The port of Capbreton is the heart of the town: fish market every morning (7am-8am, trawler arrivals), seafood restaurants along the quays (chipirons a la plancha are unmissable). The Estacade can be walked (300 m above the waves): spectacular sunset views. For surfing, the Plage de la Piste (north of Capbreton) offers ideal waves for beginners and intermediates; surf schools on site (€30-40 per lesson). The Santocha beach (south of the port) is sheltered and family-friendly. The Capbreton market (Tuesday and Saturday morning) offers local products: duck, foie gras, Landes pastis, Adour kiwis. Hossegor is 5 min on foot (cross the bridge over the Boudigau): marine lake, competition beaches (Quiksilver Pro), surf shops. In summer, the Vélodyssée cycle path runs along the coast: ideal for linking Capbreton to Hossegor, Seignosse or Vieux-Boucau (bike hire at the port).",
